                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.226/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville (<persName type="from"
                            >Motion</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-04T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 4, 1942—noon.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Referred to in the Department’s telegram number 39, April 2, 9 a.m. [<hi
                        rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]. High Commissioner agreeable to establishment of
                    Consulate at Brazzaville and delighted to accept Laurence W. Taylor as
                        Consul.<note n="90" xml:id="d547fn90">Public announcement was made on April
                        4, 1942; see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, April 4,
                        1942, p. 273.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
